The '''Bibliotheca Polyglotta''' is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[database]] for [[Multilingualism]] project, [[French language]] and science per [[global history]] at the [[University of Oslo]]. The aim of the project is according to pages is ''"producing a web corpus of Buddhist texts for using in multilingual lexicography. More generally, will the texts used for the study [[Sanskrit]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]] and [[Classical Tibetan|Tibetan]]."''

